📘 Task 5: Cybersecurity Awareness
Files: Task 5 Phishing.docx, Task 5 Preventation Checklist.docx, Task 5 Project review.docx

Phishing Case Study:

Definition and how attacks work (urgency, fake websites, credential theft).

Real-world example: COVID-19 scams in India.

Targets: students, elderly, less tech-aware individuals.

Consequences: financial loss, identity theft, privacy breaches.

Prevention Checklist:

Strong passwords + 2FA.

Avoid public Wi-Fi for sensitive accounts.

Never share OTPs or UPI PINs.

Report cybercrime via cybercrime.gov.in or helpline 1930.

Reflection:

Surprise: How convincing phishing messages can be (official logos, urgent language).

Habit to Change: Verifying links and sources before clicking; using two-factor authentication.

Communication Lesson: Poor communication in group projects can cause confusion; clear, structured messages
and shared documents help avoid issues.

